# AgentSquad credentials — v1.2 single-key setup
# Copy this file: cp .env.team.example ~/.agent-team/.env.team
# Then: chmod 600 ~/.agent-team/.env.team
# Get your key at: aistudio.google.com → Get API Key → Create in new project named "agentsquad"
#
# NEVER commit ~/.agent-team/.env.team to git.
# This .example file is safe to commit — it contains no real keys.

GEMINI_API_KEY=your_key_here

# ── Optional: per-agent key overrides for independent quota pools ─────────────
# Uncomment and fill ONLY if using separate Google accounts per agent.
# When set, these override GEMINI_API_KEY for their respective agent only.
# The Makefile uses $(or $(GEMINI_KEY_BACKEND),$(GEMINI_API_KEY)) — no code changes needed.
#
# GEMINI_KEY_BACKEND=your_key_here
# GEMINI_KEY_FRONTEND=your_key_here
# GEMINI_KEY_QA=your_key_here
# GEMINI_KEY_DEVOPS=your_key_here
# GEMINI_KEY_CONSULTANT=your_key_here
# GEMINI_KEY_RESERVE_1=your_key_here
